'''Nelida Cabigayan''' (a.k.a. Commander Lina) was a member of the [[New People's Army]] who fought the dictatorship of [[Ferdinand Marcos]] in the [[Philippines]]. She was active in NPA for two years in the early 1970s, and became regarded as folk hero. She surrendered in 1974, and act that was considered as a major coup of the Marcos' government.<ref>Salmonson, Jessica Amanda, Bibliography:''The Encyclopedia of Amazons'' (Paragon House, 1991), 45. {{ISBN|1-55778-420-5}}</ref>
