{{Infobox government agency |agency_name = Nevada Health Link |logo = |formed = |jurisdiction = [[Health insurance marketplace]] for U.S. state of [[Nevada]] |chief1_name = |chief1_position = |website = [https://www.nevadahealthlink.com/ www.nevadahealthlink.com] }} '''Nevada Health Link''' is the [[health insurance marketplace]] for the U.S. state of Nevada. The exchange enables individuals and small businesses to purchase health insurance at federally subsidized rates.{{fact|date=November 2013}}
==Background== Health insurance exchanges were established as a part of the 2010 [[Patient Protection and Affordable Care Act]] to enable individuals to purchase health insurance in state-run marketplaces.<ref name=lewis>{{cite web |url=http://www.informationweek.com/news/healthcare/policy/231001432 |title=HHS Proposes Health Insurance Exchange Rules |last=Lewis |first=Nicole |work=Information Week |date=July 12, 2011 |accessdate=November 16, 2012 }}</ref> In this legislation, states could choose to establish their own health insurance exchanges; if they choose not to do so, the federal government would run the exchange for the state.<ref name=lewis/>
