{{Other uses||Eyes of the Heart (disambiguation){{!}}Eyes of the Heart}}
{{italic title}}
'''''The Eyes of the Heart: Seeking a Path for the Poor in the Age of Globalization''''' is a book written by [[Jean-Bertrand Aristide]] about the effects of [[globalization]] on [[Haiti]].  Aristide takes the position that globalization is not a positive factor in the world, and he cites the [[World Bank]] and the [[International Monetary Fund]] as contributing to the economic downfall of Haiti.  This book was co-written by Laura Flynn,<ref>[https://www.worldcat.org/title/eyes-of-the-heart-seeking-a-path-for-the-poor-in-the-age-of-globalization/oclc/43287398 ''The Eyes of the Heart: Seeking a Path for the Poor in the Age of Globalization''. Worldcat library] </ref> and published in 2000 by Common Courage Press.

